XCode 11 supports Metal libraries.

1. Add a new build target to your project.

[![enter image description here][1]][1]


2. Add metal files in compile sources

[![enter image description here][2]][2]

3. If you use Core Image add these linker flags. Change deployment targets (ios12+ ) and check for fast math.

[![enter image description here][3]][3]

4. To your original project target add new dependencies and copy script




    cp &quot;${TARGET_BUILD_DIR}&quot;/*.metallib &quot;${METAL_LIBRARY_OUTPUT_DIR}&quot;

[![enter image description here][6]][6]

Optional:

Avoiding hard coded strings everywhere in project. Add xconfig file to project 

