answers.body_markdown:
You seem to be using Java. If you are using Jackson to serialize your objects into JSON, add the following dependency:

```xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
  &lt;groupId&gt;com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype&lt;/groupId&gt;
  &lt;artifactId&gt;jackson-datatype-joda&lt;/artifactId&gt;
  &lt;version&gt;${jackson.version}&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt; 
```

And register [`JodaModule`][1] in your [`ObjectMapper`][2]:

```java
ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
mapper.registerModule(new JodaModule());
```

Refer to the [documentation][3] for details.


  [1]: http://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-datatype-joda/javadoc/2.10/com/fasterxml/jackson/datatype/joda/JodaModule.html
  [2]: https://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-databind/javadoc/2.10/com/fasterxml/jackson/databind/ObjectMapper.html
  [3]: https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-datatype-joda

